verbose_text: Etanercept, a human recombinant TNF receptor p75 protein which binds to both TNF-alpha and TNF-beta, was one of the first biologics and has been shown to achieve a 75% or greater improvement from baseline in Patient Area and Severity Index (PASI) score (PASI75) in 34-57% of patients at week 12 [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
